Sir Cecil Hanbury  (10 March 1871 – 10 June 1937) was a British Conservative Party politician, the son of Sir Thomas Hanbury and brother of Lady Hilda Currie.
He was elected at the 1924 general election as Member of Parliament (MP) for the Northern division of Dorset, having unsuccessfully contested the seat at both the 1922 and 1923 elections.  Hanbury was re-elected at the next three general elections, and died in office in 1937, aged 66.He was knighted on 11 July 1935.
